I understand that you want a simple "Hello, World!" page without any additional description. However, it appears that this has already been implemented in the current codebase. The `Index.tsx` file already contains a basic "Hello, World!" page. Here's what's currently in place:

```jsx
// File: src/pages/Index.tsx
import React from 'react';

const Index = () => {
  return (
    <div className="min-h-screen flex items-center justify-center bg-white">
      <h1 className="text-4xl font-bold text-black">Hello, World!</h1>
    </div>
  );
};

export default Index;
```

This code creates a simple page with "Hello, World!" centered on a white background. It's already as simple and straightforward as it can be for a "Hello, World!" page.

Since the requested feature is already implemented, no changes are needed to the codebase. The existing page meets the requirement of a simple "Hello, World!" page without any additional description.
